    • Method Detail

      • onVideoConfigFrame

        void onVideoConfigFrame(byte[] parameterBuffer,
                        int bufferLen)
        Called with H.264 NAL SPS/PPS configuration data encountered by a video encoder. This method or onParameterSets(byte[], byte[]) must be called before any video frames are sent to the video sink.
        Parameters:
        parameterBuffer - The SPS/PPS parameter data.
        bufferLen - The length of parameter buffer, in bytes.

      • onParameterSets

        void onParameterSets(byte[] spsBuffer,
                     byte[] ppsBuffer)
        Allows direct specification of the Sequence Parameter Set (SPS) and Picture Parameter Set (PPS) buffers. This method or onVideoConfigFrame(byte[], int) must be called before any video frames are sent to the video sink. Calling the getByteBuffer method of the MediaFormat class using the "csd-0" key returns the SPS buffer; using the "csd-1" key returns the PPS buffer.
        Parameters:
        spsBuffer - The Sequence Parameter Set buffer.
        ppsBuffer - The Picture Parameter Set buffer.

      • onVideoFrame

        void onVideoFrame(long timecode,
                  byte[] buffer,
                  android.media.MediaCodec.BufferInfo bufferInfo)
        Called for each frame of video produced by a video encoder.
        Parameters:
        timecode - The frame timecode, in milliseconds.
        buffer - The encoded H.264 video buffer.
        bufferInfo - Per buffer metadata in the associated codec (output) buffer
